    mdxType: "MDXLayout"
  }), mdx("p", null, "Toy cars and construction sets intrigued me since I was a little boy. When I was five years old, I already tried to repair broken toys. Disassembling and fixing toys was more fun for me than just playing with them! No wonder I ended up being a programmer. I grew up in a post-Soviet state, everything was under turmoil; when I was growing up, we didn\u2019t have money nor possibilities to spend it. There was no LEGO Technics and other western toys. Instead, we had our own, made in former Czechoslovakia."), mdx("h2", {
